<br>
Social will not work without Capitalism. They are forever tied, hand in hand.<br>
(Insert Socialism here)..You cannot give away something you have none of. <br>
Free education, sure great, they would be truley a good thing to happen to those who cannot afford to pay for it. But whose going to pay the teachers who are to teach it? And if that is figured out, &quot;the payer albiet&quot; Whose the one giving the money? Oh ...wait... what is that you say... we dont have the money? Hmm looks like we need to rasie the money for that to occur. ( insert Capitalism right here).<br>
<br>
(Insert Socialsm here)<br>
Free Health Care, Man that would be just &quot;peachy&quot;.<br>
Hmm need a cure, gotta find someone who can discover, or be able to research it. Hmmm.. he's gonna need equipment..... hmmm he's gonna need help.... hmm gonna need funding for all of this... and I think we should have some of the brightest ( see first example on education).....to get it to go forward. Oh wait... this is going to need to be &quot;FUNDED&quot;...( Insert Capitalism right here).<br>
<br>
Get the idea yet?<br>
The 2 will forever be intertwined. Sorry but thats the truth. While the Ideal ( of Socialism) in its basic concept is good, and why Capitalism is good in that it supports the &quot;Ideal&quot;... there is one thing that has always ( and it was said earlier in this LONG forum).. and forever will rear its ugly head. ( and for those of you misconstrued and decided to seperate the two).. is Greed. ( not laziness AND Greed. Laziness IS  Greed. Greed of ones lifestyle ( good or bad) and not wanting to change it, knowing that it can be if one tries and has the willingness to make it so.<br>
<br>
Granted some of the worlds countries poorrest people dont have to much to choose from in the way of changing their lifes to make it better. So I'm not including that. THose are true area's that need the help of general countries that have the ability to help. Dont give them just food and water, teach them to farm and cultivate.<br>
<br>
TO forcefully make those that have come to the realization, that in order to make it NICE, or BETTER for those around us less fortunate(not by choice or course), that befreo we can help them you HAVE to help yourself. This is another one of those common sense things that people often skip. I see alot of smart, intelligent people, that lack common sense.<br>
<br>
To those of you posting on this discussion about how we should take care of everyone in the world regardless of their desicisions ( I dont see you turning your PC off that you just used to post here and selling it and then giving that money away to them). Stop you;re only fooling yourself, in fact you probably just logged on to EQ to play a few more hours.<br>
<br>
And for those you can search web sites and get definitions, and other &quot;critically' interesting data.<br>
However interesting or &quot; smart&quot; it might look, to those who are informed and have thought deeply about these things, and or experienced them... know better. It wont help you.<br>
And finally a lesson in politics that might help. ( take it with a grain of salt)...<br>
Communism is the Ideal of Socialism... at Gunpoint.<br>
